They discussed possibility of a count "vote by vote" in Michoacán
According to data from the PREP the difference between first and second place in the election of Governor is of just 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total records.
The possibility of counting "vote by vote" is a reality in it refers to the election of this year in Michoacan, where according to the data from the program of preliminary electoral results (PREP) the difference between first and second place in the election of Governor is of just 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total records.
In this regard, the President of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (IEM), Maria of the angels Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, just the past November 9, the electoral body approved a series of guidelines in order to harmonize local standards with federal electoral reform.
It will be recalled, Michoacán not formalized its political Constitution nor its Electoral Code of the State or its Justice Electoral law, given that the State Congress approved reforms shortly before concluding the legal time limit so that they could enter into force in the present electoral process and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted its publication within the deadlines provided for in the law of the official newspaper of the State, on the grounds that he had some objections.
9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice (SCJN) solved the constitutional dispute promoted by the local legislature and described as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the State representative to the constitutional reforms, since it has no right to "punish them or veto them".
Interviewed about the possibility of "vote by vote", Maria of the angels Llanderal explained that the realization of full and partial counts the vote by the local electoral body will be possible with the adoption of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of the IEM.
Thus, the partial count of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may be given on the assumptions that: the results of the proceedings do not coincide; There is the Act of counting and computation in the dossier of the box or not held by the President of the same; or, where there are mistakes or obvious alterations of records.
In addition, the total count of the vote received in all the boxes of the election may be made when there is indication that the difference between the alleged winning candidate of the election concerned and which obtained the second place in the vote, is equal to or less than one percentage point; always and when at the beginning of the meeting there is the request of the representative of the party or coalition that ran to the second of the above candidates.
The total vote count may also be performed if at the end of the regular computer establishes the difference between the allegedly winning candidate and located in second place is equal or less than one percentage point, provided there is the request expressed by the representative of the political party whose candidate came second, case in which the electoral packages that have undergone partial recount will be excluded.
It is worth mentioning that in such a situation is the choice of Morelia, where according to the difference between the first and second PREP is only the 0.16 per cent, without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total records.
