Asphalt of the UNAM would avoid potholes
Rafael Herrera, researcher at the Faculty of chemistry of the UNAM, develops asphalt modified with polymers to produce a mixture with better performance, regardless of environmental conditions and temperature
If signals that sends the pavement were met, it would not be necessary to repair nearly 200 thousand potholes every rainy season in the metropolitan area of the Valley of Mexico, warned Rafael Nájera Herrera, researcher of the Faculty of Chemistry (CF) of the UNAM, who assured that if the process of construction and maintenance of asphalt pavement is the appropriatepotholes could be reduced in amount or even eliminated altogether.
In his lecture A technological view of potholes, issued within the framework of the international year of chemistry, unveiled the laboratory responsible develops asphalt modified with polymers to produce a mixture with similar characteristics to the asphalt, but with greater mechanical resistance, both high and low temperatures.
Nájera Herrera felt that this type of modified asphalt could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, as some cities in the North of the country, to improve their performance and therefore the formation of potholes.
He explained that the asphalt, the heaviest part of the oil, is a set of molecules of hydrocarbons, a high molecular weight, called asphaltene and other low molecular weight, called maltenos, which together give the pavement their characteristic behavior memory foam.
Memory foam asphalt behaviour is that at high temperatures, around 180 degrees, behaves like a liquid, at 120 degrees Celsius the viscosity is very high and 50 degrees centigrade presents an almost solid state, while at very low temperatures, the road becomes brittle, it added.
This means that on the streets the resistance of asphalt is not uniform, but that will change during the day according to the environmental conditions and temperature, warned the specialist in chemical engineering.
CF researcher noted that the streets of the city of Mexico are mostly covered by flexible pavement, which is composed of six layers of materials, of which the last three involving the asphalt.
Among the more superficial layers is the asphalt, composed of small stones bathed in asphalt and then packed.
Each of the pebbles which constitutes the folder, he noted, is bathed with asphalt.
Transit vehicles and generate efforts, this allows forces to be disseminated very well on pavement.
They would if it were modified asphalt be they disseminated even better, felt the chemical engineer.
On the asphalt, it added, is placed a last layer called folder of Raceway, which is made up of a fine stone material, i.e., an arena that also bathes in asphalt.
As it is the layer that will be in contact with the wheels of vehicles, must you have more mechanical strength than the asphalt and provide friction on the road.
To be part of the pavement will receive and impart the efforts, the Raceway folder, also requires, have the appropriate thickness and material of which it is made must be careful.
The climate, especially the humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially the water, he said, because it significantly affects the performance of the asphalt.
When the ground is moistened, water spreads the folder inside and out, this causes a softening of all layers of the pavement and, therefore, the formation of potholes is difficult.
In the process of formation of a pothole, he said, the first to wear out is the film of bearing and only later affects the asphalt, but damage does not happen instantaneously, but it is a process that should attend the first signs with appropriate maintenance programmes.
Also member of the national system of researchers explained that vehicular pollution is another important factor in the formation of potholes and, therefore, the thickness of each layer of the pavement must go always under vehicular load and ensure full compliance, to avoid potholes forming frequently.
Rafael Herrera warned that there is still much to investigate and work on the asphalt, for example, asphalt emulsions, that in other countries they are even in the market and allow to repair potholes with ease and without using high temperatures.
